I can confirm that both `SKGLView` and `SKCanvasView` in `SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor` implement `IDisposable` with a non-virtual `Dispose()` method, and neither class is sealed. This means subclasses cannot override `Dispose()` to add custom cleanup logic.

The standard .NET fix would be to adopt the `Dispose(bool disposing)` pattern:

```csharp
public void Dispose()
{
    Dispose(true);
    GC.SuppressFinalize(this);
}

protected virtual void Dispose(bool disposing)
{
    if (disposing)
    {
        // existing cleanup
    }
}
```

As a workaround, subclasses can hide `Dispose` using the `new` keyword, though this doesn't provide polymorphic disposal:

```csharp
public new void Dispose()
{
    MyResource?.Dispose();
    base.Dispose();
}
```
